post_text:
It is important that every Arizonan does their part to prevent the spread of COVID-19, which includes wearing a mask whenever you are in public, washing your hands frequently, and maintaining physical distance from others.

We want to ensure every Arizonan has access to face masks and we have partnered with Hanes to provide free face masks to Arizonans. We encourage anyone in a vulnerable population, who is a student (or parents on behalf of students) or school staff member, or who may not be able to purchase a mask to place an order below. Each order will provide 5 washable, reusable cloth face masks, one order per household. If you have questions about ordering or for information about how this program works, visit their FAQs page.

https://azdhs.gov/preparedness/epidemiology-disease-control/infectious-disease-epidemiology/index.php#novel-coronavirus-order-masks

post_text:
We would like to thank all of our families for believing in our wonderful team of educators to support your child in their education. It has been difficult lately with the surge in COVID cases as well as the uncertainty surrounding our communities opening back up and returning to normal.

Our mission is to start in the least disruptive way possible. Skyline Education and its schools have decided it's in the best interest of our students and families to begin instruction online at our regularly scheduled date of August 3, 2020. Skyline has the online education platform in place and with survey feedback received from families, we feel we can improve upon our delivery.

To view the entire letter about school reopening go to: https://www.skylineschools.com/covid-19-updates/
